#Â Config Tamata workshop for Raspberry Pi

# Install NODEJS / NPM

#### NodeJs ( Version = )  

>     curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_7.x | sudo -E bash -  
>     sudo apt install nodejs  

#### NPM Package Install 'V.O.O1'

If problem with proxy config

>     npm config set registry http://registry.npmjs.org/ --global

# MOSQUITTO Server & Client Install
>     
     sudo apt-get install mosquitto
     wget http://repo.mosquitto.org/debian/mosquitto-repo.gpg.key
     sudo apt-key add mosquitto-repo.gpg.key
     cd /etc/apt/sources.list.d/
     sudo wget http://repo.mosquitto.org/debian/mosquitto-wheezy.list
     sudo -i 
     apt-get update 
     apt-get install mosquitto 
     apt-get install mosquitto-clients


# Install Ntp
>    sudo apt-get install ntp

### Config
>    sudo vi /etc/ntp.conf  

Update file with : 

>    server europe.pool.ntp.org  
>    restrict 10.3.141.0 mask 255.255.0.0  
>    broadcast 10.3.141.255  

### Restart Service
>    sudo service ntp restart  

# Writing service script for Spiru
## Into : /lib/systemd/system write a file ( TamataWorkshop_Spiru.service )

     [Unit]
      Description=TamataSpiru
      After=multi-user.target

      [Service]
      Type=idle
      ExecStart=/usr/bin/node /home/pirate/workshop/save_data_spiru.js

      [Install]
      WantedBy=multi-user.target

## Declare service  
      sudo systemctl enable TamataWorkshop_Spiru.service  

## Start service  
      sudo systemctl start TamataWorkshop_Spiru.service  